Senior Mechanical Engineer
Job Seekers
|
|
what:
where:
Abu Dhabi
My client is a large, multinational oil operator. With over 35 years experience, they operate out of Abu Dhabi and control assets onshore and across shallow waters. They currently have several vacancies across many of their departments. They are specifically looking for a Senior Mechanical Engineer to work for them on either a Staff or Rotational basis.
The Senior Mechanical Engineer would mainly be responsible for evaluating and recommending pre-engineering and engineering concepts, designs and development for mechanical systems and plants associated with their oil and gas production, pressure maintenance, transport and export. They would also be charged with ensuring technical integrity and HSE requirements are met in a cost effective manner. Ideal candidates will have knowledge of; Mechanical systems and plants, oil and gas gathering flowlines and manifolds, separation storage, pumping facilities, offshore loading facilities, piping and pipeline systems, mechanical packages, water and gas injection facilities.
It is expected that candidates will have a B.Sc in Mechanical Engineering with at least 12 years' experience in design and development of oil and gas related projects. This is a fantastic opportunity for the right person to join this global and still growing company, and work amongst a team of oil and gas professionals. They are offering incredibly generous salaries, plus full ex-pat packages.
If you think this is the right opportunity for you, please apply today by following the on-screen links!
